# Example requests for the Fund Transfer API

## Create a Transfer
POST http://localhost:8000/api/v1/transfers
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sourceAccountNumber": "ACC1000000001",
  "destinationAccountNumber": "ACC1000000002",
  "amount": "250.00",
  "description": "Payment for services rendered"
}

###

## Get Transfer by Reference Number
GET http://localhost:8000/api/v1/transfers/TXN20231201120000ABC123

###

## Get Account Transactions
GET http://localhost:8000/api/v1/transfers/account/ACC1000000001?limit=20

###

## Get Account Details
GET http://localhost:8000/api/v1/accounts/ACC1000000001

###

## Get Account Balance
GET http://localhost:8000/api/v1/accounts/ACC1000000001/balance

###

## List All Active Accounts
GET http://localhost:8000/api/v1/accounts

###

## Health Check
GET http://localhost:8000/health

###

## Test: Transfer with Insufficient Funds
POST http://localhost:8000/api/v1/transfers
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sourceAccountNumber": "ACC1000000001",
  "destinationAccountNumber": "ACC1000000002",
  "amount": "999999.00",
  "description": "This should fail"
}

###

## Test: Transfer with Invalid Account
POST http://localhost:8000/api/v1/transfers
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sourceAccountNumber": "INVALID123",
  "destinationAccountNumber": "ACC1000000002",
  "amount": "100.00"
}

###

## Test: Transfer with Same Source and Destination
POST http://localhost:8000/api/v1/transfers
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sourceAccountNumber": "ACC1000000001",
  "destinationAccountNumber": "ACC1000000001",
  "amount": "100.00"
}

###

## Test: Transfer with Negative Amount
POST http://localhost:8000/api/v1/transfers
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sourceAccountNumber": "ACC1000000001",
  "destinationAccountNumber": "ACC1000000002",
  "amount": "-100.00"
}
